rest_of_day_open: Well, it is Friday, so as soon as I get off from work, I will feel free and I will get a surge of energy that will make me feel very outgoing and positive all through the weekend.  I am a bit nervous since I am throwing a virtual birthday party for my husband, and I have never done anything like that, but it should be fun.
critical_positive: What worked well is that my partner was very kind, accepting, a great conversationalist, and she seemed to feel comfortable letting me take the lead and she was very gracious even though I feel like I kind of overpowered the conversation.  Hopefully she does not feel unheard or that I made things awkward for her, since she was very lovely.
critical_negative: There really was nothing that I could say did not work well, with the very distinct exception that since she was so accommodating and gracious, she may not have told me exactly how she felt about me domineering the conversation.  I do wish slightly that I would have let her talk more.

rest_of_day_open: I think there will be an uptick in positive happenstances and productivity, such as socializing more with family and friends, and abiding my time with work for the first time in months. Towards the end there might be a downside with some negative emotions due to me having to wrap some things up I've been delaying all year.
critical_positive: The topic was something we both coincidentally picked and prepped about, and it was a common thing that we were both learning about at different stages so the back and forth was really informative for both people, me especially. I was given a lot of great recommendations and she was a great listener and conversationalist.
critical_negative: I could've have spoken up more or geared the topic to something I was a bit more knowledgeable of - but then there is the drawback of not gaining anything out of the conversation, so even then, I think the conversations low points were still high. Perhaps I could've prepped a bit more so I could contribute more vocally.
